.TH ROK "1" "March 2026" "rok 0.5.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rok \- Run One, Know All - Execute multi-step tasks from JSON

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rok
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
rok is a CLI tool that executes multi-step tasks defined in JSON format.

.SH COMMANDS

.SS templates
List available templates

.SS init-template [\fIname\fR]
Create a new template interactively

.SS validate-template [\fIpath\fR]
Validate a template schema

.SS run \fItask\-name\fR
Run a saved task

.SS save \fIname\fR
Save current payload as a named task

.SS list
List saved tasks

.SS edit \fItask\-name\fR
Edit a saved task

.SS watch
Watch files and re-run on changes

.SS history
Show execution history

.SS replay [\fIrun\-id\fR]
Replay a previous execution

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR=\fIFILE\fR
Path to JSON file

.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR=\fIJSON\fR
JSON payload inline

.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR=\fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: json, pretty, silent (default: json)

.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Preview steps without executing

.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose output

.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress output (except errors)

.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help message

.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version

.SH EXAMPLES

Run a task from a file:
.PP
.nf
\fBrok\fR \-f task.json
.fi

.PP
Run from stdin:
.PP
.nf
echo '\fB{"steps":[{"type":"bash","cmd":"echo hello"}]}' | \fBrok\fR
.fi

.PP
List available templates:
.PP
.nf
\fBrok\fR templates
.fi

